[code]aClass16_Sub1_Sub1_Sub2_881.method288(c / 2 - 90, 0xffffff, anInt1163, k, true, "Username: " + aString1045 + ((anInt1236 == 0) & (anInt1174 % 40 < 20) ? "@yel@|" : ""));[/code]

This is the "Username Box" code^. You know what box I'm talkin about. If you don't, why are you even reading this?


[code]aClass16_Sub1_Sub1_Sub2_881.method288[/code]

This is the [b]actual[/b] method that draws the box...but what's all that BS in the brackets?


[code](c / 2 - 90, 0xffffff, anInt1163, k, true, "Username: " + aString1045 + ((anInt1236 == 0) & (anInt1174 % 40 < 20) ? "@yel@|" : ""))[/code]

"0xffffff" is just the text color, which would be white.

"Username:" is the text that says...Yes! That's right Timmy! "Username:". 

"aString1045" Is added right after username..must be where you put your password.


"((anInt1236 == 0) & (anInt1174 % 40 < 20) ? "@yel@|" : ""))"

This is what creates the flashing marker after the text. If int1236 is 0, and 1174/40 is less than 20, then it creates the marker, if not, not. Well, that's certainly one way to do it.

Now scroll down a wee bit, past where the password box is created, and you should see

